    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - LIFT AXLE SYSTEMS - CONTROLS - PNEUMATIC CONTROL SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="14">
        <title>PNEUMATIC CONTROL SYSTEM</title>
        <para>The lift axle control systems contain both pneumatic and electrical components. The electrical control
            system is covered in the
            <hotlnk document="s14019_37.xml" xrefid="hl14019075">ELECTRICAL CONTROL SYSTEM</hotlnk>
            section
            <xref refid="hl14019075"/>. The
            <emph type="underscr">operation</emph>
            of the pneumatic controls is described in the sections covering each axle type;
            <hotlnk document="s14019_15.xml" xrefid="hl14019050">FIXED AXLE ASSEMBLIES</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="hl14019050"/>, or
            <hotlnk document="s14019_24.xml" xrefid="hl14019060">SELF-STEERING AXLE ASSEMBLIES</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="hl14019060"/>. Removal and installation procedures for all axle mounted control components are
            located in the sections covering each axle type. Removal and installation procedures for all cab mounted
            control components are located in the REMOVAL and INSTALLATION sections in this section. The following
            figures are provided to identify air line routing for the lift axle systems.
        </para>
